Text.SourceString: Oh, the new neighbor.//<portrait=happy>So, someone really <Italic>was</> moving into town, huh?//<portrait=normal>I didn’t believe it until I saw you myself.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, the new neighbor.//<portrait=happy>So, someone really <Italic>was</> moving into town, huh?//<portrait=normal>I didn’t believe it until I saw you myself.

Text.SourceString: I don’t often go to the part of the island where your farm is.//<portrait=annoyed>It was overgrown the last time I visited. Just a mess.//How is it so far?
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t often go to the part of the island where your farm is.//<portrait=annoyed>It was overgrown the last time I visited. Just a mess.//How is it so far?

Text.SourceString: The salon is closed today, my dear. <NPCName>Erika</> is busy volunteering at the school.
Text.LocalizedString: The salon is closed today, my dear. <NPCName>Erika</> is busy volunteering at the school.

Text.SourceString: I quite like my hair today.
Text.LocalizedString: I quite like my hair today.

Text.SourceString: If you’re looking for easy dish ideas, try this.//You can put fruit and vegetables on a grill, then drizzle them with honey for a fantastic, colorful meal!
Text.LocalizedString: If you’re looking for easy dish ideas, try this.//You can put fruit and vegetables on a grill, then drizzle them with honey for a fantastic, colorful meal!

Text.SourceString: The assorted grilled platter is my all-time favorite.
Text.LocalizedString: The assorted grilled platter is my all-time favorite.

Text.SourceString: It’s crunchy and sweet.//<portrait=normal>Easy to toss together after a long day of work.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s crunchy and sweet.//<portrait=normal>Easy to toss together after a long day of work.

Text.SourceString: There should be plenty of wild mushrooms or berries around the school. I haven’t checked today, though.
Text.LocalizedString: There should be plenty of wild mushrooms or berries around the school. I haven’t checked today, though.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Eva’s</> a talented baker. She reminds me a lot of <NPCName>Betty</>.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Eva’s</> a talented baker. She reminds me a lot of <NPCName>Betty</>.

Text.SourceString: Too bad <NPCName>Betty</> doesn’t bake anymore.//<portrait=normal>I do miss her pastries sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: Too bad <NPCName>Betty</> doesn’t bake anymore.//<portrait=normal>I do miss her pastries sometimes.

Text.SourceString: Remember to eat your greens, <PlayerName>$player</>.//The more color on your plate, the better.
Text.LocalizedString: Remember to eat your greens, <PlayerName>$player</>.//The more color on your plate, the better.

Text.SourceString: That sounds nosy, I know.//<portrait=normal>It’s still good advice.
Text.LocalizedString: That sounds nosy, I know.//<portrait=normal>It’s still good advice.

Text.SourceString: If <NPCName>Sam</> stopped bringing in supplies from the mainland, maybe more people would start farming again.
Text.LocalizedString: If <NPCName>Sam</> stopped bringing in supplies from the mainland, maybe more people would start farming again.

Text.SourceString: I may talk to him about it, but I don’t know if that would be the right call.//<portrait=concerned>Probably not.
Text.LocalizedString: I may talk to him about it, but I don’t know if that would be the right call.//<portrait=concerned>Probably not.

Text.SourceString: Inhale…exhale… I’m trying to relax a little.
Text.LocalizedString: Inhale…exhale… I’m trying to relax a little.

Text.SourceString: You should take off your boots and be one with nature.//Take a deep breath…
Text.LocalizedString: You should take off your boots and be one with nature.//Take a deep breath…

Text.SourceString: You didn’t take off your boots.
Text.LocalizedString: You didn’t take off your boots.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes we forget to consider the most important opinion when we make big decisions – our own.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes we forget to consider the most important opinion when we make big decisions – our own.

Text.SourceString: It’s your voice that matters most, my dear. Listen to it first, then consider others.//Try not to get it confused. I know I sometimes do.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s your voice that matters most, my dear. Listen to it first, then consider others.//Try not to get it confused. I know I sometimes do.

Text.SourceString: I know this may sound random, but I just want to say that sometimes things don’t make sense, and that’s okay.//Oh, you’re so full of energy and have so much ahead of you.
Text.LocalizedString: I know this may sound random, but I just want to say that sometimes things don’t make sense, and that’s okay.//Oh, you’re so full of energy and have so much ahead of you.

Text.SourceString: What a wonderful prospect!
Text.LocalizedString: What a wonderful prospect!

Text.SourceString: Stew is easy to make. It’s also impossible to mess up.//It was one of the first meals I learned to cook.
Text.LocalizedString: Stew is easy to make. It’s also impossible to mess up.//It was one of the first meals I learned to cook.

Text.SourceString: Have you tried your luck in the kitchen?
Text.LocalizedString: Have you tried your luck in the kitchen?

Text.SourceString: I feel like going foraging tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel like going foraging tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: Oh no! I have work tomorrow.//<portrait=concerned>Maybe over the weekend. That’s better for running around the island.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh no! I have work tomorrow.//<portrait=concerned>Maybe over the weekend. That’s better for running around the island.

Text.SourceString: Do you know who <NPCName>Lily</> reminds me of? Take a guess!//<portrait=happy>Oh, this is fun.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you know who <NPCName>Lily</> reminds me of? Take a guess!//<portrait=happy>Oh, this is fun.

Text.SourceString: <Italic>Yes!</> <NPCName>Jim</>! They look so much alike.//<portrait=normal>That girl has her dad’s smile. Which is rare.
Text.LocalizedString: <Italic>Yes!</> <NPCName>Jim</>! They look so much alike.//<portrait=normal>That girl has her dad’s smile. Which is rare.

Text.SourceString: I prefer decor that has a meaningful story over something that’s brand new and clean looking.
Text.LocalizedString: I prefer decor that has a meaningful story over something that’s brand new and clean looking.

Text.SourceString: That feels empty to me.//<portrait=happy>But of course, sometimes there are exceptions.
Text.LocalizedString: That feels empty to me.//<portrait=happy>But of course, sometimes there are exceptions.

Text.SourceString: We donate what we can to Starlet Town. Mayor <NPCName>Connor</> is very grateful.
Text.LocalizedString: We donate what we can to Starlet Town. Mayor <NPCName>Connor</> is very grateful.

Text.SourceString: As the saying goes, “Sunday clears away the rust of the week.”//<portrait=normal>Oh! What a fun thing to say!
Text.LocalizedString: As the saying goes, “Sunday clears away the rust of the week.”//<portrait=normal>Oh! What a fun thing to say!

Text.SourceString: I believe everything happens for a reason, be it good or bad.
Text.LocalizedString: I believe everything happens for a reason, be it good or bad.

Text.SourceString: We learn from both good things and bad.
Text.LocalizedString: We learn from both good things and bad.

Text.SourceString: You can improve your cooking skills by watching the cooking channel. They show reruns sometimes, though.//That’s a bit of a bummer, especially when you’re looking forward to a new recipe.
Text.LocalizedString: You can improve your cooking skills by watching the cooking channel. They show reruns sometimes, though.//That’s a bit of a bummer, especially when you’re looking forward to a new recipe.

Text.SourceString: I suppose if you miss an episode, it’s good that they rerun it.
Text.LocalizedString: I suppose if you miss an episode, it’s good that they rerun it.

Text.SourceString: I don’t shop much at Socket & Pan. It’s not to my taste.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t shop much at Socket & Pan. It’s not to my taste.

Text.SourceString: My hair is my signature, you know. I’ve worn it like this since I was a bachelorette.
Text.LocalizedString: My hair is my signature, you know. I’ve worn it like this since I was a bachelorette.

Text.SourceString: Goodness knows, that was a long time ago. I tried growing it out one time, but it just wasn’t me.
Text.LocalizedString: Goodness knows, that was a long time ago. I tried growing it out one time, but it just wasn’t me.

Text.SourceString: I collect lots of things. Antique furniture, for example. I’m always in the market for that.
Text.LocalizedString: I collect lots of things. Antique furniture, for example. I’m always in the market for that.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Ben</> has a stunning collection. You never know when he’ll have something new. Hmm…
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Ben</> has a stunning collection. You never know when he’ll have something new. Hmm…

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Sam</> and I are going dancing at the Tavern tomorrow night. You should join us!
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Sam</> and I are going dancing at the Tavern tomorrow night. You should join us!

Text.SourceString: Oh, I hope <NPCName>Theo</> is there! He has such a fabulous voice!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, I hope <NPCName>Theo</> is there! He has such a fabulous voice!

Text.SourceString: I believe everything happens for a reason, be it good or bad.
Text.LocalizedString: I believe everything happens for a reason, be it good or bad.

Text.SourceString: We learn from both good things and bad.
Text.LocalizedString: We learn from both good things and bad.

Text.SourceString: Oh my. I need to get my hair done. I can’t possibly go out like this!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh my. I need to get my hair done. I can’t possibly go out like this!

Text.SourceString: My hairspray doesn’t hold all day. I should write the company and let them know. What a disaster!
Text.LocalizedString: My hairspray doesn’t hold all day. I should write the company and let them know. What a disaster!

Text.SourceString: Ah, you’d think it would be easier for us to get the groceries we need, what with owning a general store and all.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, you’d think it would be easier for us to get the groceries we need, what with owning a general store and all.

Text.SourceString: It’s easier for us than the general public, true.//But we still rely a lot on local farmers like you, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s easier for us than the general public, true.//But we still rely a lot on local farmers like you, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: I went to look for shallots near the lake yesterday. But nothing. Maybe I should check again today and see if they’ve sprouted.
Text.LocalizedString: I went to look for shallots near the lake yesterday. But nothing. Maybe I should check again today and see if they’ve sprouted.

Text.SourceString: I should check around the mayor’s house for shallots tomorrow. It’s already the last week of Summer.
Text.LocalizedString: I should check around the mayor’s house for shallots tomorrow. It’s already the last week of Summer.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Sam’s</> in the mood for fried rice, and it isn’t the same without fresh shallots.//<portrait=concerned>If you ever make it yourself, you’ll agree.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Sam’s</> in the mood for fried rice, and it isn’t the same without fresh shallots.//<portrait=concerned>If you ever make it yourself, you’ll agree.

Text.SourceString: Oh my! I could do with a little rain right now.//The heat is destroying my hair!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh my! I could do with a little rain right now.//The heat is destroying my hair!

Text.SourceString: Ah, I’m being dramatic again. I think I’ll cool off and have some ice cream or something.//<portrait=annoyed>The heat is making me fuzzy.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, I’m being dramatic again. I think I’ll cool off and have some ice cream or something.//<portrait=annoyed>The heat is making me fuzzy.

Text.SourceString: Are you ready for snow season? The kids are going to love it. //<portrait=happy>They usually go to that park over there and build snowmen. Ah!
Text.LocalizedString: Are you ready for snow season? The kids are going to love it. //<portrait=happy>They usually go to that park over there and build snowmen. Ah!

Text.SourceString: I hope Winter isn’t as cold this year.//<portrait=normal>I can’t seem to find my wool gloves anywhere.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope Winter isn’t as cold this year.//<portrait=normal>I can’t seem to find my wool gloves anywhere.

Text.SourceString: You know, <PlayerName>$player</>, as part of my New Year’s resolution, I’m going to complain less.//I have an excellent feeling about next year!
Text.LocalizedString: You know, <PlayerName>$player</>, as part of my New Year’s resolution, I’m going to complain less.//I have an excellent feeling about next year!

Text.SourceString: The key is to find more activities to keep myself busy.//<portrait=normal>The less free time I have, the less I’ll have to complain about. You should try that.
Text.LocalizedString: The key is to find more activities to keep myself busy.//<portrait=normal>The less free time I have, the less I’ll have to complain about. You should try that.

Text.SourceString: I might go to the lake later. Rainy days are perfect for berry hunting.//Can you guess why?
Text.LocalizedString: I might go to the lake later. Rainy days are perfect for berry hunting.//Can you guess why?

Text.SourceString: Less competition, correct! Great minds think alike, they say.
Text.LocalizedString: Less competition, correct! Great minds think alike, they say.

Text.SourceString: You don’t mind the rain, I see.
Text.LocalizedString: You don’t mind the rain, I see.

Text.SourceString: I really should rest. I’m starting to feel sleepy.
Text.LocalizedString: I really should rest. I’m starting to feel sleepy.

Text.SourceString: How about the rain, huh? How are we supposed to go on like this?
Text.LocalizedString: How about the rain, huh? How are we supposed to go on like this?

Text.SourceString: Ah, I’m being dramatic.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, I’m being dramatic.

Text.SourceString: Storming again? Seriously, how are we going to survive this Winter if the sun keeps hiding like this?
Text.LocalizedString: Storming again? Seriously, how are we going to survive this Winter if the sun keeps hiding like this?

Text.SourceString: I just wish there were something we could do about it.
Text.LocalizedString: I just wish there were something we could do about it.

Text.SourceString: You don’t mind the storm, I see.
Text.LocalizedString: You don’t mind the storm, I see.

Text.SourceString: What a storm, huh?//How are we supposed to go on like this?
Text.LocalizedString: What a storm, huh?//How are we supposed to go on like this?

Text.SourceString: Ah, I’m being dramatic.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, I’m being dramatic.

Text.SourceString: How’s your Winter been so far? I hope the cold and mountains of snow don’t discourage you.
Text.LocalizedString: How’s your Winter been so far? I hope the cold and mountains of snow don’t discourage you.

Text.SourceString: Snowing again? Seriously, how are we going to survive this Winter if the sun keeps hiding like this?
Text.LocalizedString: Snowing again? Seriously, how are we going to survive this Winter if the sun keeps hiding like this?

Text.SourceString: I just wish there were something we could do about it.
Text.LocalizedString: I just wish there were something we could do about it.

Text.SourceString: You don’t mind the snow, I see.
Text.LocalizedString: You don’t mind the snow, I see.

Text.SourceString: We mix the dyes here ourselves. All organic, without any harsh chemicals.
Text.LocalizedString: We mix the dyes here ourselves. All organic, without any harsh chemicals.

Text.SourceString: Gosh, I sound like a salesperson. Ha ha!
Text.LocalizedString: Gosh, I sound like a salesperson. Ha ha!

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Erika</> and I don’t have set customers, exactly.//But people usually have a preference for who works on their hair.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Erika</> and I don’t have set customers, exactly.//But people usually have a preference for who works on their hair.

Text.SourceString: Is business good at the farm, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Is business good at the farm, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: I have to mention this before I forget.//<portrait=normal>I had a feeling you’d visit today, for some odd reason. I’m glad you did. My instincts never fail me.
Text.LocalizedString: I have to mention this before I forget.//<portrait=normal>I had a feeling you’d visit today, for some odd reason. I’m glad you did. My instincts never fail me.

Text.SourceString: I have a little free time before my errands this morning.
Text.LocalizedString: I have a little free time before my errands this morning.

Text.SourceString: I’ve developed a habit of winding down with a cup of green tea after a long day of work.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve developed a habit of winding down with a cup of green tea after a long day of work.

Text.SourceString: My gut tells me today is going to be a relaxing day.
Text.LocalizedString: My gut tells me today is going to be a relaxing day.

Text.SourceString: Something told me to come here.
Text.LocalizedString: Something told me to come here.

Text.SourceString: Maybe it’s greenery I’ve been longing for lately.//<portrait=normal>My body is craving nature.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe it’s greenery I’ve been longing for lately.//<portrait=normal>My body is craving nature.

Text.SourceString: I’m going to take it easy and eat only raw food today.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m going to take it easy and eat only raw food today.

Text.SourceString: Don’t you think a boutique hotel sort of thing would do splendidly here?
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t you think a boutique hotel sort of thing would do splendidly here?

Text.SourceString: It’s too nice to stay inside today, isn’t it?
Text.LocalizedString: It’s too nice to stay inside today, isn’t it?

Text.SourceString: No, I’m not a diver. But you go ahead! I’m a Sagittarius, you know. Fire and water don’t mix.
Text.LocalizedString: No, I’m not a diver. But you go ahead! I’m a Sagittarius, you know. Fire and water don’t mix.

Text.SourceString: But you probably need to go to the other side of the island to dive.
Text.LocalizedString: But you probably need to go to the other side of the island to dive.

Text.SourceString: I have to read for half an hour or so before going to bed. It’s become a habit, I think.//I can’t just close my eyes and fall asleep.
Text.LocalizedString: I have to read for half an hour or so before going to bed. It’s become a habit, I think.//I can’t just close my eyes and fall asleep.

Text.SourceString: I have mixed feelings about putting a TV in our bedroom.//I feel like it might be too much of a distraction.
Text.LocalizedString: I have mixed feelings about putting a TV in our bedroom.//I feel like it might be too much of a distraction.

Text.SourceString: That’s a very good point. It is convenient.
Text.LocalizedString: That’s a very good point. It is convenient.

Text.SourceString: Oh, you should have seen this place! It was overgrown before Mayor <NPCName>Connor</> decided to bring everybody together to clean it up a bit.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, you should have seen this place! It was overgrown before Mayor <NPCName>Connor</> decided to bring everybody together to clean it up a bit.

Text.SourceString: And look how pretty it is now. People can have a picnic here.
Text.LocalizedString: And look how pretty it is now. People can have a picnic here.

Text.SourceString: I filled a basket full of wild fruit and flowers. There were plenty near the shrine, over there.
Text.LocalizedString: I filled a basket full of wild fruit and flowers. There were plenty near the shrine, over there.

Text.SourceString: Have you found any flowers? Oh dear. I sure hope I didn’t pick them all. There were plenty earlier.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you found any flowers? Oh dear. I sure hope I didn’t pick them all. There were plenty earlier.

Text.SourceString: It’s too nice to stay inside today, isn’t it?
Text.LocalizedString: It’s too nice to stay inside today, isn’t it?

Text.SourceString: Your grandparents’ farm was neglected for a long time. You should have seen it! It wasn’t a pretty sight.//Mayor <NPCName>Connor</> was going to turn it into a community garden before you moved in.
Text.LocalizedString: Your grandparents’ farm was neglected for a long time. You should have seen it! It wasn’t a pretty sight.//Mayor <NPCName>Connor</> was going to turn it into a community garden before you moved in.

Text.SourceString: I’m glad you did, by the way. Now someone will take care of the land.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m glad you did, by the way. Now someone will take care of the land.

Text.SourceString: Can I get you anything?
Text.LocalizedString: Can I get you anything?

Text.SourceString: *busily arranging shelves*
Text.LocalizedString: *busily arranging shelves*

Text.SourceString: I have to go to work soon. Let me just finish up with this shelf.
Text.LocalizedString: I have to go to work soon. Let me just finish up with this shelf.

Text.SourceString: This sauce is delicious! I wonder what <NPCName>Frank</> puts in it.
Text.LocalizedString: This sauce is delicious! I wonder what <NPCName>Frank</> puts in it.

Text.SourceString: It could use a little chilling before serving. Then it would be just right.
Text.LocalizedString: It could use a little chilling before serving. Then it would be just right.

Text.SourceString: Do I talk to <NPCName>Noah</> or <NPCName>Frank</> about it? Who’s in charge tonight?
Text.LocalizedString: Do I talk to <NPCName>Noah</> or <NPCName>Frank</> about it? Who’s in charge tonight?

Text.SourceString: They need to turn up the volume a little, don’t you think, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: They need to turn up the volume a little, don’t you think, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: Do I talk to <NPCName>Noah</> or <NPCName>Frank</> about it? Who’s in charge tonight?
Text.LocalizedString: Do I talk to <NPCName>Noah</> or <NPCName>Frank</> about it? Who’s in charge tonight?

Text.SourceString: I don’t tell <NPCName>Sam</> how to handle his store, but please tell him if a purchase isn’t up to your standards.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t tell <NPCName>Sam</> how to handle his store, but please tell him if a purchase isn’t up to your standards.

Text.SourceString: If you’d rather, feel free to tell me. I’m all ears when it comes to customer complaints.//I wish other businesses would handle complaints like I do, to be honest.
Text.LocalizedString: If you’d rather, feel free to tell me. I’m all ears when it comes to customer complaints.//I wish other businesses would handle complaints like I do, to be honest.

Text.SourceString: Running the salon takes a lot of my time. There’s maintenance to consider, and ordering as well.//Even when I’m not there, I still think about it.
Text.LocalizedString: Running the salon takes a lot of my time. There’s maintenance to consider, and ordering as well.//Even when I’m not there, I still think about it.

Text.SourceString: You don’t want a leak when you have a salon. It could run up a massive water bill.
Text.LocalizedString: You don’t want a leak when you have a salon. It could run up a massive water bill.

Text.SourceString: The key is to make sure the salon is well maintained.
Text.LocalizedString: The key is to make sure the salon is well maintained.

Text.SourceString: I cut my hair often. Every other week at least.
Text.LocalizedString: I cut my hair often. Every other week at least.

Text.SourceString: Just a little trim helps. It isn’t easy to keep up with short hair.//It becomes fairly obvious as it grows out. The unevenness. Goodness gracious!
Text.LocalizedString: Just a little trim helps. It isn’t easy to keep up with short hair.//It becomes fairly obvious as it grows out. The unevenness. Goodness gracious!

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Sam</> inherited the store from his dad. I’m sure some people, like the mayor, still remember it as Remi’s.//<NPCName>Sam</> changed the name to simplify things.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Sam</> inherited the store from his dad. I’m sure some people, like the mayor, still remember it as Remi’s.//<NPCName>Sam</> changed the name to simplify things.

Text.SourceString: Remi is my father-in-law, that’s right.
Text.LocalizedString: Remi is my father-in-law, that’s right.

Text.SourceString: The snow makes you think, doesn’t it?//It’s one thing not to have something in the first place. But it’s another thing to have it and then have it taken away so quickly.
Text.LocalizedString: The snow makes you think, doesn’t it?//It’s one thing not to have something in the first place. But it’s another thing to have it and then have it taken away so quickly.

Text.SourceString: Thank <NPCName>Goddess</> I have a full schedule at my salon. What a perfect way to keep me busy.
Text.LocalizedString: Thank <NPCName>Goddess</> I have a full schedule at my salon. What a perfect way to keep me busy.

Text.SourceString: I get to meet people and chat with my customers. I can’t think of a better job for someone like me.
Text.LocalizedString: I get to meet people and chat with my customers. I can’t think of a better job for someone like me.

Text.SourceString: I love <NPCName>Sam</> dearly, but I can’t bring myself to work at the store for too long.//<NPCName>Goddess</> help me, it’s so dull.
Text.LocalizedString: I love <NPCName>Sam</> dearly, but I can’t bring myself to work at the store for too long.//<NPCName>Goddess</> help me, it’s so dull.

Text.SourceString: Bless <NPCName>Eva</>. She’s a dear to actually like being in the store as much as <NPCName>Sam</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Bless <NPCName>Eva</>. She’s a dear to actually like being in the store as much as <NPCName>Sam</>.

Text.SourceString: I help with the store’s inventory when I have free time. I check the shelves and restock, but that’s all.
Text.LocalizedString: I help with the store’s inventory when I have free time. I check the shelves and restock, but that’s all.

Text.SourceString: Oh dear. I just know I wouldn’t enjoy having more responsibility than that. I prefer working directly with customers.//Computers put me right to sleep.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh dear. I just know I wouldn’t enjoy having more responsibility than that. I prefer working directly with customers.//Computers put me right to sleep.

Text.SourceString: Ever since we were young, <NPCName>Sam</> and I always knew we wanted to have two or maybe even four children, like <NPCName>Betty</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Ever since we were young, <NPCName>Sam</> and I always knew we wanted to have two or maybe even four children, like <NPCName>Betty</>.

Text.SourceString: The thought of running around with small children, taking them to the beach, teaching them how to dive… It was exciting for us.
Text.LocalizedString: The thought of running around with small children, taking them to the beach, teaching them how to dive… It was exciting for us.

Text.SourceString: A big family was always an exciting idea for me. <NPCName>Sam</> comes from one, whereas I grew up without any siblings.// Sometimes, I feel like I missed out on that.
Text.LocalizedString: A big family was always an exciting idea for me. <NPCName>Sam</> comes from one, whereas I grew up without any siblings.// Sometimes, I feel like I missed out on that.

Text.SourceString: *laughs* On a lighter note, his family is very fun to be around.//I want that!
Text.LocalizedString: *laughs* On a lighter note, his family is very fun to be around.//I want that!

Text.SourceString: I’m not big on cooking, but I do watch the cooking channel every once in a while.//Cooking I can do. Baking is a little harder to grasp.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not big on cooking, but I do watch the cooking channel every once in a while.//Cooking I can do. Baking is a little harder to grasp.

Text.SourceString: It reminds me of the whole jelly and jam mess.//So similar, yet so different.
Text.LocalizedString: It reminds me of the whole jelly and jam mess.//So similar, yet so different.

Text.SourceString: It feels good to move on. Sometimes, closure is what we need. And acceptance is the first step.
Text.LocalizedString: It feels good to move on. Sometimes, closure is what we need. And acceptance is the first step.

Text.SourceString: In my case, anyway. And I’m glad I did.
Text.LocalizedString: In my case, anyway. And I’m glad I did.

Text.SourceString: I hope <NPCName>Ben</> has some unique antiques. I’m in the market for some tables to put in the guest room.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope <NPCName>Ben</> has some unique antiques. I’m in the market for some tables to put in the guest room.

Text.SourceString: Perhaps I could put some paintings in there too. Hang some of <NPCName>Dippa’s</> originals on the wall.
Text.LocalizedString: Perhaps I could put some paintings in there too. Hang some of <NPCName>Dippa’s</> originals on the wall.

Text.SourceString: I have my hands full right now. I’m not thinking about having children at the moment.
Text.LocalizedString: I have my hands full right now. I’m not thinking about having children at the moment.

Text.SourceString: I don’t think we’re ready for it after– *sighs* Anyway, maybe someday.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t think we’re ready for it after– *sighs* Anyway, maybe someday.

Text.SourceString: I’ve been thinking about redoing the house completely! Perhaps I could reconfigure the rooms and make a huge living room.//Or maybe I could turn the space into a yoga studio.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been thinking about redoing the house completely! Perhaps I could reconfigure the rooms and make a huge living room.//Or maybe I could turn the space into a yoga studio.

Text.SourceString: That seems unnecessary, though, since we have a perfectly good place to work out together in the community center over there.
Text.LocalizedString: That seems unnecessary, though, since we have a perfectly good place to work out together in the community center over there.

Text.SourceString: I have work tomorrow. I think I have some appointments.
Text.LocalizedString: I have work tomorrow. I think I have some appointments.

Text.SourceString: After work? Hmm. I don’t think we have anything special planned.//But I have to confirm with <NPCName>Sam</>.
Text.LocalizedString: After work? Hmm. I don’t think we have anything special planned.//But I have to confirm with <NPCName>Sam</>.

Text.SourceString: You could at least use a trim, my dear. Hmm…
Text.LocalizedString: You could at least use a trim, my dear. Hmm…

Text.SourceString: You should try wigs! It’s a great way to change up your look without too much commitment.
Text.LocalizedString: You should try wigs! It’s a great way to change up your look without too much commitment.

Text.SourceString: Some of our furniture is from <NPCName>Ben</>. They’re antiques, you see.
Text.LocalizedString: Some of our furniture is from <NPCName>Ben</>. They’re antiques, you see.

Text.SourceString: I might visit him later.
Text.LocalizedString: I might visit him later.

Text.SourceString: I should retire to the living room. Would you care to join me?
Text.LocalizedString: I should retire to the living room. Would you care to join me?

Text.SourceString: I’m not a diver. I don’t like water. But you go ahead!//I’m a Sagittarius, you know. Fire and water don’t mix.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not a diver. I don’t like water. But you go ahead!//I’m a Sagittarius, you know. Fire and water don’t mix.

Text.SourceString: But you probably need to go to the other side of the island to dive.//<portrait=normal>There isn’t a diving site around here.
Text.LocalizedString: But you probably need to go to the other side of the island to dive.//<portrait=normal>There isn’t a diving site around here.

Text.SourceString: The evenings are so quiet here. It would have been nice with a couple of kids around.
Text.LocalizedString: The evenings are so quiet here. It would have been nice with a couple of kids around.

Text.SourceString: Now that the nursery is no longer a nursery, what should I do with the room, do you think?
Text.LocalizedString: Now that the nursery is no longer a nursery, what should I do with the room, do you think?

Text.SourceString: Maybe I should leave it empty for now.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe I should leave it empty for now.

Text.SourceString: Would you like some berries, <PlayerName>$player</>? They’re a bit messy to eat, though.
Text.LocalizedString: Would you like some berries, <PlayerName>$player</>? They’re a bit messy to eat, though.

Text.SourceString: Ah, I hate to stain my fingers. But I can’t resist! Just look how juicy they are.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, I hate to stain my fingers. But I can’t resist! Just look how juicy they are.

Text.SourceString: Mayor <NPCName>Connor</>, bless his heart, had good intentions for turning your lot into a community garden. With the former owner’s approval, of course.//But do you really think people would walk there every single day to garden?
Text.LocalizedString: Mayor <NPCName>Connor</>, bless his heart, had good intentions for turning your lot into a community garden. With the former owner’s approval, of course.//But do you really think people would walk there every single day to garden?

Text.SourceString: I honestly don’t know if putting a community garden that far from town would work, if we’re being honest with ourselves here.
Text.LocalizedString: I honestly don’t know if putting a community garden that far from town would work, if we’re being honest with ourselves here.

Text.SourceString: Your livestock must be happy to be able to run around on such a massive plot of land.
Text.LocalizedString: Your livestock must be happy to be able to run around on such a massive plot of land.

Text.SourceString: I should have gone to the lake instead. The vibe here is too jarring today.
Text.LocalizedString: I should have gone to the lake instead. The vibe here is too jarring today.

Text.SourceString: The town gets so quiet when it rains. As if it’s telling us to slow down, forcing us to take a break.
Text.LocalizedString: The town gets so quiet when it rains. As if it’s telling us to slow down, forcing us to take a break.

Text.SourceString: Do people even buy this oil? We could do with better quality, for sure.
Text.LocalizedString: Do people even buy this oil? We could do with better quality, for sure.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Erika</> should already be at the salon. I go in around noon. I don’t usually take morning appointments anyway.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Erika</> should already be at the salon. I go in around noon. I don’t usually take morning appointments anyway.

Text.SourceString: Mayor <NPCName>Connor</>, bless his heart, had good intentions for turning your lot into a community garden. With the former owner’s approval, of course.//But do you really think people would walk there every single day to garden?
Text.LocalizedString: Mayor <NPCName>Connor</>, bless his heart, had good intentions for turning your lot into a community garden. With the former owner’s approval, of course.//But do you really think people would walk there every single day to garden?

Text.SourceString: We could have divided the work, true. But I honestly don’t know if putting a community garden that far from town would work, if we’re being honest with ourselves here.
Text.LocalizedString: We could have divided the work, true. But I honestly don’t know if putting a community garden that far from town would work, if we’re being honest with ourselves here.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Ben</> has a lot of healing crystals.//None of them spoke to me though. So I haven’t brought any of them home yet.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Ben</> has a lot of healing crystals.//None of them spoke to me though. So I haven’t brought any of them home yet.

Text.SourceString: I don’t like choosing crystals. I want to let one speak to my soul.//That’s the confirmation I need.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t like choosing crystals. I want to let one speak to my soul.//That’s the confirmation I need.

Text.SourceString: Winter can get pretty wet, and it’s a little too slow for a Sagittarius like myself.//It doesn’t fit well with my energy.
Text.LocalizedString: Winter can get pretty wet, and it’s a little too slow for a Sagittarius like myself.//It doesn’t fit well with my energy.

Text.SourceString: Summer fits my energy the best.
Text.LocalizedString: Summer fits my energy the best.

Text.SourceString: Today is a good day to garden.//<portrait=happy>The weather couldn’t be better.
Text.LocalizedString: Today is a good day to garden.//<portrait=happy>The weather couldn’t be better.

Text.SourceString: My energy is charged. Summer has such a positive effect on me.
Text.LocalizedString: My energy is charged. Summer has such a positive effect on me.

Text.SourceString: Now that it’s Spring, I can feel the color in my aura coming back again.//<portrait=happy>I like it.
Text.LocalizedString: Now that it’s Spring, I can feel the color in my aura coming back again.//<portrait=happy>I like it.

Text.SourceString: <Italic>You</> definitely look more glowing, <PlayerName>$Player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: <Italic>You</> definitely look more glowing, <PlayerName>$Player</>.

Text.SourceString: Ah, my aura is definitely affected by Winter.//I’m not feeling it today.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, my aura is definitely affected by Winter.//I’m not feeling it today.

Text.SourceString: I went to Raja’s Coffee Corner the other day and had some hot cocoa.//It was delicious. I had it with a muffin.
Text.LocalizedString: I went to Raja’s Coffee Corner the other day and had some hot cocoa.//It was delicious. I had it with a muffin.

Text.SourceString: I get why it’s a popular treat there.//<portrait=normal>It seems <NpcName>Raj</> figured out how to bake delicious muffins. They should try making pumpkin muffins.
Text.LocalizedString: I get why it’s a popular treat there.//<portrait=normal>It seems <NpcName>Raj</> figured out how to bake delicious muffins. They should try making pumpkin muffins.

Text.SourceString: The snow is here!//<portrait=happy>We have about three more weeks of this weather. Are you ready?
Text.LocalizedString: The snow is here!//<portrait=happy>We have about three more weeks of this weather. Are you ready?

Text.SourceString: I saw <NpcName>Oliver</> and <NpcName>Valentina</> walking to school the other day in their Winter gear.//<portrait=happy>So, so cute!
Text.LocalizedString: I saw <NpcName>Oliver</> and <NpcName>Valentina</> walking to school the other day in their Winter gear.//<portrait=happy>So, so cute!

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Erika</> gave me a book of baby names a long time ago. It was probably too early for the gift, but I loved the way she was just as excited as I was.//I couldn’t bring myself to get rid of it.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Erika</> gave me a book of baby names a long time ago. It was probably too early for the gift, but I loved the way she was just as excited as I was.//I couldn’t bring myself to get rid of it.

Text.SourceString: It reminds me of how kind and supportive she is as a friend.//It brings good memories, even after I lost the baby.
Text.LocalizedString: It reminds me of how kind and supportive she is as a friend.//It brings good memories, even after I lost the baby.

Text.SourceString: There’s a sweet scent in the air today. Hmm. Can you smell it? It’s faint.//<portrait=happy>That’s the scent of cherry blossoms blooming.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s a sweet scent in the air today. Hmm. Can you smell it? It’s faint.//<portrait=happy>That’s the scent of cherry blossoms blooming.

Text.SourceString: Coconuts are everywhere.//I know they’re all-year-round fruits here, but for some reason, they’re more visible in Summer.
Text.LocalizedString: Coconuts are everywhere.//I know they’re all-year-round fruits here, but for some reason, they’re more visible in Summer.

Text.SourceString: Coconuts are so abundant.//<portrait=normal>I’m sure there’s plenty of them in Garden Lane or on the beach, if you’re looking for any.
Text.LocalizedString: Coconuts are so abundant.//<portrait=normal>I’m sure there’s plenty of them in Garden Lane or on the beach, if you’re looking for any.

Text.SourceString: It’s not an easy job to put up festival decorations and then take them down.//Especially for the Animal Festival. There are so many different decorations!
Text.LocalizedString: It’s not an easy job to put up festival decorations and then take them down.//Especially for the Animal Festival. There are so many different decorations!

Text.SourceString: I bring cookies and drinks for the Sanchez boys while they’re putting up decorations. Can’t be easy.
Text.LocalizedString: I bring cookies and drinks for the Sanchez boys while they’re putting up decorations. Can’t be easy.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Ben’s</> out of town. He usually goes to a music festival.//I hope he brings some good items when he comes back.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Ben’s</> out of town. He usually goes to a music festival.//I hope he brings some good items when he comes back.

Text.SourceString: He should be back the first week of Winter, if you’re wondering.
Text.LocalizedString: He should be back the first week of Winter, if you’re wondering.

Text.SourceString: I spotted a few gray hairs last week.//I might leave them be. I’ll see.
Text.LocalizedString: I spotted a few gray hairs last week.//I might leave them be. I’ll see.

Text.SourceString: Next week is Winter anyway. I’ll probably be wearing a beanie most of the time.//I’ll just wait till Spring to touch up my hair.
Text.LocalizedString: Next week is Winter anyway. I’ll probably be wearing a beanie most of the time.//I’ll just wait till Spring to touch up my hair.
